The paper introduces a new class of tuple-generating dependencies (TGDs) and focuses on conjunctive query answering, which are topics typically studied in the database (cs.DB) and logic (cs.LO) communities. The paper also discusses the decidability of the new class, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions several other decidable classes, which suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC).
